41
00:01:47,890 --> 00:01:51,480
此人藐视法律
This is a man who believes in the rule of law-ish.

42
00:01:51,480 --> 00:01:55,270
不顾立法程序  罔顾宪法
The legislative process-ish. The Constitution-ish.

43
00:01:55,270 --> 00:01:57,460
这样的人应该当总统吗
Is this the man who should be president?

44
00:01:57,460 --> 00:01:59,460
邓巴女士  你像个好律师那样
Ms. Dunbar, like any good lawyer,

45
00:01:59,460 --> 00:02:02,420
有绝佳的辞令
you have a knack for rhetoric-ish.

46
00:02:02,420 --> 00:02:04,460
但美国人民听够空话了
But the American people are tired of words.

47
00:02:04,470 --> 00:02:06,910
他们渴望的是实际行动
What they crave is action.

48
00:02:07,380 --> 00:02:09,620
我担心我强调"行动"这个词
My concern about focusing on the word, "action,"

49
00:02:09,620 --> 00:02:12,750
她会用失败的行动回击
is that she'll just come back with failed actions.

50
00:02:12,750 --> 00:02:14,540
《美国就业法案》  联合国维和任务
America Works, the UN mission.

51
00:02:14,540 --> 00:02:17,230
"行动"在上轮民调的关键人群中反响不错
"Action" performed well with key demos in our last poll.

52
00:02:17,230 --> 00:02:19,430
是  但这不会偏离主题吗
Yes, but doesn't this take us off message?

53
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:21,440
我们一直说  "支持弗兰克·安德伍德
We have been saying, "A vote for Frank Underwood

54
00:02:21,440 --> 00:02:23,660
就是支持《美国就业法案》"
is a vote for America Works."

55
00:02:23,660 --> 00:02:25,470
我们一直在宣传那个
That's what we've been running on.

56
00:02:25,470 --> 00:02:27,720
你得找一个比《美国就业法案》更广的词
You need a word that goes beyond America Works.

57
00:02:27,720 --> 00:02:29,370
任何情况都能用的
Something that can be used for anything.

58
00:02:29,370 --> 00:02:30,760
雷米  你怎么看
Remy, what do you think?

59
00:02:32,540 --> 00:02:34,640
我们在讨论"行动"这个词
We're talking about the word, "action."

60
00:02:34,640 --> 00:02:35,860
抱歉  我刚刚...
Sorry, I was, uh...

61
00:02:36,810 --> 00:02:38,420
我在想外交政策的论点
my mind was on the foreign policy argument.

62
00:02:38,420 --> 00:02:40,740
-我想提前考虑好  -"愿景"怎么样
- I was just thinking ahead. - What about "vision"?

63
00:02:40,740 --> 00:02:42,660
不会太泛泛了吗
Isn't that too generic?

64
00:02:42,670 --> 00:02:44,530
就是这目的啊  越概括越好
That's what we want. I mean, the more generic, the better.

65
00:02:44,530 --> 00:02:47,390
人们可以把任何事投射到"愿景"上
People can project anything they want on "vision."

66
00:02:47,390 --> 00:02:49,240
我明天之前做好民调
I'll get it polled before tomorrow.

67
00:02:49,240 --> 00:02:50,740
下面该准备与夏普的辩论了
We should work on Sharp next.

68
00:02:50,740 --> 00:02:52,140
要我扮她吗
You want me to play her?

69
00:02:52,140 --> 00:02:54,910
谢谢你这么认真地扮演  唐纳德
Thank you for taking your role so seriously, Donald.

70
00:02:54,910 --> 00:02:57,660
你应该考虑当演员
You should consider a career on the stage.

71
