125
00:08:43,200 --> 00:08:44,370
总统先生
Mr. President.

126
00:08:44,380 --> 00:08:46,740
感谢你赶来安德鲁空军基地
Thank you for coming all the way to Andrews.

127
00:08:46,740 --> 00:08:49,090
雷米跟你说过总体方案了吗
Did Remy walk you through the broad strokes?

128
00:08:49,700 --> 00:08:52,190
不论是国际还是国内的政策问题
No matter the policy question, foreign or domestic,

129
00:08:52,190 --> 00:08:53,960
我们都抨击邓巴经验不足
we hammer Dunbar's lack of experience.

130
00:08:53,960 --> 00:08:54,930
要猛烈攻击
We bludgeon it.

131
00:08:54,930 --> 00:08:58,000
尽可能地强调"经验不足"
We cannot say "lack of experience" enough.

132
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:00,970
毫无疑问  她会提起克莱尔休会任命一事
And no doubt, she'll bring up Claire's recess appointment,

133
00:09:00,970 --> 00:09:03,880
我不能发表看法  所以这个话题就交给你
where I can't take the bait, so I leave that entirely to you.

134
00:09:03,880 --> 00:09:06,570
这正是我想跟你讨论的问题之一
This was one of the things that I was hoping to discuss.

135
00:09:06,570 --> 00:09:08,820
你不想说她性别歧视吗
Oh, you don't want to call her "sexist"?

136
00:09:08,830 --> 00:09:11,040
-这论点站不住脚  -能站住脚
- The argument doesn't hold. - It does hold.

137
00:09:11,040 --> 00:09:13,030
她说克莱尔不胜任那份工作
She says that Claire was unqualified.

138
00:09:13,030 --> 00:09:16,380
你说换了有同样履历的男人她就不会那么说
You say she wouldn't say that about a man with the same CV.

139
00:09:16,380 --> 00:09:17,460
我觉得这未必
I'm not sure that's true.

140
00:09:17,460 --> 00:09:19,180
而且指责另一位女性性别歧视
And calling another woman sexist

141
00:09:19,180 --> 00:09:20,300
特别是台上还有一位男性
when there's a man on the stage--

142
00:09:20,300 --> 00:09:22,070
没有比你更合适的人选
And who else is better but you

143
00:09:22,070 --> 00:09:24,310
指责她在女性问题上
to call her out on what she's done for women,

144
00:09:24,310 --> 00:09:25,910
根本无所作为
which is absolutely nothing?

145
00:09:25,910 --> 00:09:29,890
而通过立法促进性别平等是你的标志之一
Whereas gender-equality legislation is one of your hallmarks.

146
00:09:29,890 --> 00:09:32,180
但这对我的伤害可能远大于对她
But it could hurt me more than it hurts her.

147
00:09:33,450 --> 00:09:35,100
我以为我们已达成共识
I thought we had an understanding.

148
00:09:35,100 --> 00:09:37,670
你咄咄逼人  我保持气度
You were gonna play pit bull while I play presidential.

149
00:09:37,680 --> 00:09:40,250
你会惹火上身吗  对  有可能
Will you get a little bloody? Yes, probably.

150
00:09:40,250 --> 00:09:42,250
但这不就是辩论的目的吗
But that's what people want in their debates.

151
00:09:42,250 --> 00:09:44,870
然后你与我携手  我们一起埋了她
And then you and I together, we bury her.

152
00:09:44,870 --> 00:09:46,690
再下个星期你退选  转而支持我
You drop out next week, endorse me

153
00:09:46,690 --> 00:09:47,930
竞选就此结束
and the race is over.

154
00:09:47,930 --> 00:09:50,120
我不介意当打手
I have no problem being forceful.

155
00:09:50,120 --> 00:09:53,580
但这个性别歧视  还有择校的问题
But this sexism thing, and the whole school argument, I--

156
00:09:53,780 --> 00:09:54,560
你是说她的孩子
You mean her kids.

157
00:09:54,560 --> 00:09:56,220
我真的不想把他们扯进来
I really don't want to involve them.

158
00:09:56,220 --> 00:09:59,320
有两点我们希望美国人民知道
We have two things we want the American people to hear:

159
00:09:59,320 --> 00:10:00,560
她经验不足
she lacks experience

160
00:10:00,560 --> 00:10:02,390
还有她含着金钥匙出生
and she was born with a silver spoon in her mouth.

161
00:10:02,390 --> 00:10:03,930
但肯定还有别的办法
But there has to be another way.

162
00:10:03,930 --> 00:10:06,570
她想鼓吹同一起跑线
She wants to trumpet an equal playing field?

163
00:10:06,570 --> 00:10:09,610
那她为什么还送自己的孩子上私立学校
Then why does she send her own kids to private school?

164
00:10:09,610 --> 00:10:11,730
这是一个简单清晰的观点
That is a clear and simple argument

165
00:10:11,730 --> 00:10:13,480
所有人都能明白
that everyone can get their heads around.

166
00:10:13,480 --> 00:10:14,460
而且加分的是
And it doesn't hurt

167
00:10:14,460 --> 00:10:17,130
爱荷华州最大的雇佣单位就是公立学校系统
that Iowa's biggest employer is the public school system.

168
00:10:17,130 --> 00:10:19,800
艾伦也送他的孩子上私立学校
Alan sends his kids to private school.

169
00:10:20,710 --> 00:10:21,900
对  但他们不是你的孩子
Yeah, but they're not your kids.

170
00:10:21,900 --> 00:10:24,580
我是他们的继母  我会被批为伪君子
