00:20:02,280 --> 00:20:03,490
展现了一个清晰的愿景
with America Works,

346
00:20:03,490 --> 00:20:07,590
它是近一个世纪以来最全面的就业计划
the most comprehensive jobs program in nearly a century.

347
00:20:07,590 --> 00:20:10,270
我们已经证明该法案在华盛顿取得了成功
We showed it could work in Washington DC.

348
00:20:10,270 --> 00:20:14,330
现在我们需要将我们的成功推广到全国
We need now to take what we did there and spread it nationwide,

349
00:20:14,330 --> 00:20:18,300
这样美国梦就能真正美梦成真
so that the American dream can become the American reality.

350
00:20:18,310 --> 00:20:22,140
但是光有愿景还不够
But that vision isn't enough on its own.

351
00:20:22,140 --> 00:20:25,820
你们需要一个有经验的人来实现这份愿景
You need someone with experience to make it happen.

352
00:20:25,820 --> 00:20:28,910
考虑到我在国会和白宫的经历
And between my time in Congress and now at the White House,

353
00:20:28,910 --> 00:20:32,710
我的经验比两位对手加起来还要丰富
I have more experience than both of my opponents combined.

354
00:20:32,710 --> 00:20:35,500
当你考虑雇佣一个人的时候
And, uh, when you hire someone for a job,

355
00:20:35,500 --> 00:20:37,760
你是会选择有三十年工作经验的人
are you gonna hire someone with 30 years' experience,

356
00:20:37,760 --> 00:20:39,450
还是不到十年工作经验的人
or someone with less than ten

357
00:20:39,450 --> 00:20:42,020
还是完全没有经验的人
or someone with no experience at all?

358
00:20:42,020 --> 00:20:43,580
在我南方老家那边
Where I come from down south,

359
00:20:43,590 --> 00:20:46,430
我们管这种情况叫做显而易见
we call that as clear as a glass of moonshine.

360
00:20:50,520 --> 00:20:52,490
接下来有请前副检察长邓巴女士
Former Solicitor General Dunbar is next.

361
00:20:52,490 --> 00:20:54,660
-致开场陈述  -谢谢  约翰
- Your opening statement, please. - Thank you, John.

362
00:20:54,660 --> 00:20:56,150
也感谢爱荷华人民
And thank you Iowa.

363
00:20:56,840 --> 00:20:59,810
我同意总统刚才所说的
Well, I agree with the President.

364
00:21:00,130 --> 00:21:04,380
愿景和经验正是美国人民需要的
Vision and experience are exactly what America needs.

365
00:21:04,380 --> 00:21:05,040
不幸的是
Unfortunately,

366
00:21:05,040 --> 00:21:09,400
他拥有的是错误的愿景和糟糕的经验
he has the wrong vision and horrendous experience.

367
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:12,860
你可以说《美国就业法案》有远见  但实际上
You can call America Works visionary, but in truth,

368
00:21:12,860 --> 00:21:15,570
它只是一个存在了数十年的
it is just an ultra-conservative agenda

369
00:21:15,570 --> 00:21:17,280
极其保守的议程
that's been around for decades.

370
00:21:17,280 --> 00:21:20,870
瓦解安全保障  让人们自生自灭
Dismantle the safety net and hang people out to dry.

371
00:21:20,870 --> 00:21:22,790
至于总统先生的经验
As for the President's experience,

372
00:21:22,790 --> 00:21:24,220
他在领导层在任期间
he was in the leadership during

373
00:21:24,220 --> 00:21:28,360
正值国会历史上最低效的时期之一
one of the most ineffective decades in Congressional history.

374
00:21:28,360 --> 00:21:31,520
作为总统  他经手的每一件事都失败了
As president, he has failed at everything he's done.

375
00:21:31,520 --> 00:21:33,740
《美国就业法案》在包括我在内的
America Works was illegal in the minds

376
00:21:33,740 --> 00:21:36,940
许多法律专业人士看来都是违法的
of many legal experts, myself included.

377
00:21:36,940 --> 00:21:39,960
他的约旦河谷计划彻底失败
His Jordan Valley plan was a disaster.

378
00:21:39,960 --> 00:21:42,000
如果你把这些称为经验
If that's what you call experience,

379
00:21:42,350 --> 00:21:45,890
那你不仅是在美化履历  而是伪造履历了
you're not just padding the résumé, you are fabricating it.

380
00:21:46,500 --> 00:21:50,000
安德伍德总统并不是在向我们展示愿景
President Underwood isn't presenting us with a vision,

381
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:53,780
而是在说服自己相信自己的妄想
he is convincing himself of his own delusion.

382
00:21:53,780 --> 00:21:57,990
我的愿景则是遏制大企业的贪婪
Now, my vision is to tackle corporate greed,

383
00:21:57,990 --> 00:22:00,270
为最需要的人们提高薪酬
raise pay for those who need it most,

384
00:22:00,270 --> 00:22:03,080
通过刺激经济增长制造就业
and create jobs by growing the economy,

385
00:22:03,080 --> 00:22:06,500
而不是抢劫人民的退休金和医保
not robbing people of their retirement and health care.

386
00:22:07,040 --> 00:22:11,550
我的经验是二十年捍卫宪法的经历
My experience is 20 years defending the Constitution.

387
00:22:11,550 --> 00:22:14,230
所以你们可以肯定  当我宣誓就职时
You know when I take my presidential oath,

388
00:22:14,230 --> 00:22:17,140
我会遵守誓言的每一个字
I will mean every word of it.

389
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:23,520
邓巴女士  谢谢  夏普众议员女士
Ms. Dunbar, thank you. Congresswoman Sharp,

390
00:22:23,520 --> 00:22:25,370
-你的开场陈述  -谢谢
- your opening statement, please. - Thank you.

391
00:22:25,950 --> 00:22:29,040
很多人都知道我曾是一名美国军人
As many of you know, I am a US Army veteran.

392
00:22:29,280 --> 00:22:32,650
我曾亲睹我的战友们
Now, I've seen firsthand the great sacrifices

393
00:22:32,650 --> 00:22:36,900
为守卫这个国家做出的伟大牺牲
my fellow servicemen and women have made defending this country.

394
00:22:36,900 --> 00:22:40,270
但我怎能让他们去保卫这个
But how can we ask them to protect a system

395
00:22:40,270 --> 00:22:42,540
没在保护我们的系统
that isn't protecting us?

396
00:22:42,780 --> 00:22:43,930
比如说女性
Take women, for example.

397
00:22:43,930 --> 00:22:46,800
这儿有两名女性参与了总统竞选
There are two women at this debate running for president.

398
00:22:46,800 --> 00:22:50,720
十分了不起  可是在普通工作场合呢
That's extraordinary. But out in the general workforce?

399
00:22:50,720 --> 00:22:55,240
男性赚一美元而女性只能赚77美分
Women earn 77 cents on the dollar compared to men.

400
00:22:55,240 --> 00:22:59,870
少数裔女性甚至只有67美分
Even worse is minority women earning 67 cents on the dollar.

401
00:23:00,440 --> 00:23:04,430
邓巴女士可以高谈阔论缩小贫富差距
Now, Ms. Dunbar can talk about balancing the scales,

402
00:23:04,430 --> 00:23:08,370
但她继承了亿万家产
but she inherited a multi-billion-dollar fortune

403
00:23:08,370 --> 00:23:11,470
从未需要去努力赚一分钱
and never had to earn any cents on the dollar.

404
00:23:12,230 --> 00:23:14,160
我不认同安德伍德总统
Now, I don't agree with everything

405
00:23:14,160 --> 00:23:17,120
所做或是提议的所有事
that President Underwood has done or proposes,

406
00:23:17,120 --> 00:23:19,650
但至少他知道为生活辛苦打拼的滋味
but at least he knows what it means to work for a living.

407
00:23:19,650 --> 00:23:22,190
我还能带给你们更多
I can give you even better than that.

408
00:23:22,190 --> 00:23:25,200
我知道为生活斗争的滋味
I know what it means to fight for a living.

409
00:23:25,200 --> 00:23:28,880
我将在国内努力为公平而战
And I will fight for fairness here at home

410
00:23:28,880 --> 00:23:31,880
正如我当初在海外与敌人拼死斗争
just as fiercely as I fought our enemies overseas.

411
00:23:32,170 --> 00:23:32,930
谢谢
Thank you.

412
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:35,210
谢谢  议员女士
Thank you, Congresswoman.

413
00:23:35,210 --> 00:23:37,180
我们开始第一部分  对外政策
Let's move to part one: foreign policy.

414
00:23:37,180 --> 00:23:39,310
第一个问题是给您的  总统先生
And the first question is for you, Mr. President.

415
00:23:39,310 --> 00:23:41,760
鉴于近期约旦河谷多变的形势
Given the recent volatile events in the Jordan Valley,

416
00:23:41,760 --> 00:23:43,420
您仍然认为集结
do you still believe it was correct

417
00:23:43,420 --> 00:23:45,420
联合国多国军队进行干预  是正确的决定吗
to assemble the United Nations coalition and to intervene,

418
00:23:45,420 --> 00:23:48,930
或者我们该承认此次行动是错误的
or is it time now to call that intervention a mistake?

419
00:23:49,080 --> 00:23:50,550
我会回答这个问题的  约翰
Well, I will answer that question, John,

420
00:23:50,550 --> 00:23:51,610
但我首先需要反驳
but I'd like to address first

421
00:23:51,610 --> 00:23:53,990
邓巴女士刚刚说的一些话
something Ms. Dunbar said a few moments ago.

422
00:23:53,990 --> 00:23:57,800
《美国就业法案》不是陈旧保守的议程
America Works is not some stale, old, conservative agenda.

423
00:23:57,800 --> 00:23:59,770
你能说出一个共和党人
You name me one Republican

424
00:23:59,940 --> 00:24:01,970
曾建议我们拿联邦基金
who has suggested using federal funds

425
00:24:01,970 --> 00:24:04,570
为每一个想要工作的美国人
to guarantee jobs for every American

426
00:24:04,570 --> 00:24:07,280
提供工作  我就把帽子吃了
who wants one and I will eat my hat.

427
00:24:07,640 --> 00:24:09,810
这不是在瓦解政府  这是在...
This isn't about dismantling government. It is about--

428
00:24:09,810 --> 00:24:12,670
我们不是该讨论对外政策吗
Aren't we supposed to be talking about foreign policy?

429
00:24:13,180 --> 00:24:14,540
我会谈到的  但首先
Yeah, I will. But first,

430
00:24:14,540 --> 00:24:16,460
-我想纠正一下...  -因为谈论
- I'd like to correct... - because it's easier to talk about

431
00:24:16,460 --> 00:24:17,420
《美国就业法案》
America Works

432
00:24:17,420 --> 00:24:19,850
比维护你站不住脚的联合国行动更容易
than to defend your indefensible UN mission.

433
00:24:19,850 --> 00:24:21,950
至少我有可维护的过去  邓巴女士
At least I have a record to defend, Ms. Dunbar.

434
00:24:21,950 --> 00:24:23,810
说到过去  总统先生
Speaking of your record, Mr. President,

435
00:24:23,810 --> 00:24:27,260
您曾公开表明不会竞选总统
you went on record saying you wouldn't run for president.

436
00:24:27,260 --> 00:24:28,820
-可却还是参选了  -约翰  看起来
- And yet here you are. - John, it seems that

437
00:24:28,820 --> 00:24:31,070
你精心制定的规则已经失效了
your very thoughtful rules have gone out the window.

438
00:24:31,070 --> 00:24:33,130
您对规则毫不尊重  总统先生
You have no respect for rules, Mr. President.

439
00:24:33,130 --> 00:24:34,440
比如联邦应急管理署
Take FEMA, for example.

440
00:24:34,440 --> 00:24:36,070
你现在要说联邦应急管理署
Oh, you want to talk about FEMA now

441
00:24:36,070 --> 00:24:37,240
而非对外政策了吗
instead of foreign policy.

442
00:24:37,240 --> 00:24:39,440
我只是顺着您的话往下接
I am just following your lead, sir.

443
00:24:39,440 --> 00:24:40,430
看我们在您的领导下
See what a mess we get into

444
00:24:40,430 --> 00:24:42,680
陷入怎样的混乱啊
when we follow your brand of leadership?

445
00:24:43,900 --> 00:24:45,560
我必须承认  邓巴女士
Well, I must admit that Ms. Dunbar

446
00:24:45,560 --> 00:24:48,000
确实在辞令华丽的辩论方面
does have many years of experience

447
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:50,960
有多年经验
making rhetorical arguments in court.

448
00:24:50,960 --> 00:24:53,630
今天看到的就是最好的证明
You've just seen proof of that today.

449
00:24:53,630 --> 00:24:56,900
可是服务美国人民并非靠口头上的功夫
But serving the American people is not about what you say,

450
00:24:56,900 --> 00:24:58,320
而在于行动
it's about what you do.

451
00:24:58,320 --> 00:25:01,420
我想问  你做了什么
And I would ask: what have you ever done?

452
00:25:01,420 --> 00:25:05,210
我同意  邓巴女士经验的缺乏令人担心
I have to agree that Ms. Dunbar's lack of experience is a concern.

453
00:25:05,210 --> 00:25:07,450
总统居然提起经验的重要性
I find it ironic that the president talks about

454
00:25:07,450 --> 00:25:08,960
讽刺的是
the importance of experience,

455
00:25:09,010 --> 00:25:12,090
他任命了毫无任何资质的妻子
given the fact that he appointed his wife UN ambassador

456
00:25:12,100 --> 00:25:14,340
为联合国大使
despite her utter lack of credentials.

457
00:25:14,340 --> 00:25:16,230
这是性别歧视
That's a sexist comment.

458
00:25:16,830 --> 00:25:18,100
你说什么
Excuse me?

459
00:25:18,100 --> 00:25:20,030
如果是一名女性总统任命自己的丈夫
You wouldn't be making that argument

460
00:25:20,040 --> 00:25:22,790
你肯定不会这么说
if a female president had appointed her husband.

461
00:25:22,790 --> 00:25:25,590
一个像克莱尔·安德伍德那样缺乏
A husband with the same lack of international affairs experience

462
00:25:25,590 --> 00:25:27,020
外交经验的丈夫吗  我还是会的
as Claire Underwood? Yes, I would.

463
00:25:27,020 --> 00:25:31,120
事实上  这让我质疑你对于女性的支持  
In fact, it makes me question your advocacy for women in general.

464
00:25:31,120 --> 00:25:32,650
真荒谬
Well, that's ridiculous.

465
00:25:32,650 --> 00:25:35,230
你在推动性别平等方面做过什么
What have you done to further gender equality?

466
00:25:35,230 --> 00:25:38,180
你在缩小贫富差距方面做过什么
What have you done to balance the scales?

467
00:25:38,180 --> 00:25:39,760
那是你的口号
That's your slogan, and yet

468
00:25:39,760 --> 00:25:42,160
可你却无视了一半的人口
you've left half of the population out of the mix.

469
00:25:42,160 --> 00:25:43,560
事实不是这样的
But that is simply not true.

470
00:25:43,560 --> 00:25:45,890
你能说出一件事吗
Can, can you name one specific thing?

471
00:25:45,890 --> 00:25:49,600
当然  我是史上少有的
Yes, I can. Being a woman, who has served as Solicitor General,

472
00:25:49,600 --> 00:25:51,700
曾担任过副检察长的女性
one of the few in the history of the court.

473
00:25:51,700 --> 00:25:53,360
这符合你个人的利益
Well, that advanced your interests,

474
00:25:53,360 --> 00:25:56,510
可那对于1.5亿女性有什么用呢
but what did that do for 150 million women out there?

475
00:25:56,510 --> 00:25:58,560
身为女性能够担任这样的职位
The very fact that a woman can hold that position--

476
00:25:58,560 --> 00:26:02,080
-那么你是一种象征  -某种程度上我是
- So you are a symbol. - In a way, yes, I suppose I am.

477
00:26:02,080 --> 00:26:04,650
包括你在内的很多女性
Me and many other women, including yourself--

478
00:26:04,650 --> 00:26:06,310
可这样能够让我们
Okay, but how does that get us

479
00:26:06,310 --> 00:26:08,730
从挣77美分变成一美元吗
from 77 cents on the dollar to 100?

480
00:26:08,730 --> 00:26:10,240
真实的钱  不是象征意义的
Real cents. Not symbolic cents.

481
00:26:10,240 --> 00:26:12,900
你现在只是在模仿总统的说辞
Well, now you're just aping the president's rhetoric.

482
00:26:12,900 --> 00:26:15,080
又是性别歧视
Another sexist comment.

483
00:26:15,080 --> 00:26:19,410
-你怎么可以这么扭曲我的话  -我只代表自己
- How could you possibly misconstrue my words? - I speak for myself.

484
00:26:19,410 --> 00:26:21,850
我不是在模仿总统  或者任何男人
I am not aping the president or any other man.

485
00:26:21,850 --> 00:26:23,670
抱歉  我不会回应这种...
I'm sorry, I won't engage with this--

486
00:26:23,670 --> 00:26:25,760
战场上  战事激烈的时候
You know, when things get tough on the battlefield,

487
00:26:25,760 --> 00:26:27,240
我们可不会说
we never say,

488
00:26:27,240 --> 00:26:29,130
"抱歉  我不会回应[开火]"
"Sorry, I won't engage."

489
00:26:29,130 --> 00:26:31,540
我们做出回应  邓巴女士
We engage, Ms. Dunbar.

490
00:26:33,590 --> 00:26:36,920
而你得面对这个事实
And you need to confront the fact

491
00:26:36,920 --> 00:26:40,640
那就是你并未把女性的利益放在心上
that you do not have women's best interests at heart.

492
00:26:40,920 --> 00:26:42,590
约翰  这样没法收场了
John, this is getting out of hand.

493
00:26:42,590 --> 00:26:44,590
好吧  开始下一个问题
All right, then let's move on to the next question.

494
00:26:44,870 --> 00:26:47,530
现在的辩论主题是外交政策
We are in the foreign policy portion of this debate.

495
00:26:47,530 --> 00:26:49,510
邓巴女士  请允许我问你这个问题
Ms. Dunbar, let me bring this question to you.

496
00:26:49,510 --> 00:26:50,650
你不赞成总统的做法
You're critical of the president.

497
00:26:50,650 --> 00:26:53,010
你说他在约旦河谷的所作所为完全站不住脚
You say it's indefensible, what he has done in the Jordan Valley.

498
00:26:53,010 --> 00:26:55,160
-对  -如果换做是你  你具体会怎么做呢
- That's right. - But specifically, what would you do differently?

499
00:26:55,160 --> 00:26:57,220
约翰  我很高兴你问了这个问题
Well, John, I'm glad you asked that.

500
00:26:57,230 --> 00:26:58,810
在我看来  把军队派往
Sending troops into the

501
00:26:58,810 --> 00:27:01,980
-约旦河谷算不上外交  -我得回酒店了
- Jordan Valley isn't what I call diplomacy. - I need to go back to the hotel.

502
00:27:01,980 --> 00:27:06,390
各位  安德伍德夫人得走了
Everybody, Mrs. Underwood needs to leave us now.

503
00:27:06,390 --> 00:27:07,640
真希望我可以留下来
I really wish I could stay,

504
00:27:07,640 --> 00:27:09,170
但我明天的行程很满
but I have a very full day tomorrow.

505
00:27:09,170 --> 00:27:11,800
我得回去休息了  不过我想再次感谢所有人
I should rest up. But again, I want to thank you all

506
00:27:11,800 --> 00:27:14,070
感谢你们的招待还有你们的辛勤工作
for your hospitality and all of your hard work.

507
00:27:14,070 --> 00:27:15,340
非常感谢各位
Thank you so much.

508
00:27:16,970 --> 00:27:18,180
大家晚安
Good night, everyone.

509
00:27:23,150 --> 00:27:28,830
他的滴入式外交政策只不过是又一个妄想
His trickle-down diplomacy is another example of delusion.

510
00:27:29,580 --> 00:27:30,460
安德伍德夫人
Mrs. Underwood.

511
00:27:32,210 --> 00:27:34,470
你该回去  跟志愿者待在一起
Oh, you should go back inside with the volunteers

512
00:27:34,480 --> 00:27:36,600
体验竞选的每个方面
and have the full campaign experience.

513
00:27:36,600 --> 00:27:38,330
我来新罕布什尔不是为了这个
I didn't come to New Hampshire for that.

514
00:27:38,330 --> 00:27:39,490
我是来找你谈话的
I came to speak with you.

515
00:27:40,180 --> 00:27:42,990
也许明天吧  我现在不太清醒
Tomorrow, maybe. My brain is a bit fried.

516
00:27:42,990 --> 00:27:44,300
是因为夏普的话吗
Is it what Sharp said?

517
00:27:44,300 --> 00:27:45,960
你是为这个看不下去了吗
Why you don't want to watch anymore?

518
00:27:46,010 --> 00:27:48,920
-那个性别歧视的发言  -我不关心那个
- The sexist comment? - Oh, I honestly don't care.

519
00:27:48,920 --> 00:27:50,340
那不过是一场表演
It's all spectacle.

520
00:27:50,340 --> 00:27:52,080
看谁能拉到更多支持率  不是吗
Who can get the most points, right?

521
00:27:52,560 --> 00:27:53,370
晚安
Good night.

522
00:27:56,350 --> 00:27:58,360
现在进行辩论的第二部分  国内政策
Now for part two of our debate: the domestic agenda.

523
00:27:58,360 --> 00:28:00,580
第一个问题是给你的  议员女士
And the first question goes to you, Congresswoman.

524
00:28:00,580 --> 00:28:02,650
总统提到了《美国就业法案》
The President speaks of America Works.

525
00:28:02,650 --> 00:28:04,530
邓巴女士想要提高最低工资
Ms. Dunbar wants to raise minimum wage.

526
00:28:04,530 --> 00:28:06,310
她提到了控制高管薪酬
Talks about regulating executive pay.

527
00:28:06,310 --> 00:28:07,860
但很多人还不清楚
But a lot of people aren't quite clear

528
00:28:08,080 --> 00:28:09,410
你主张的经济政策
about your economic policy.

529
00:28:09,410 --> 00:28:11,400
具体来说  我特别强调"具体"
What specifically, I underscore "Specifically,"

530
00:28:11,400 --> 00:28:13,420
你若当选总统会怎么做
would you do if elected president?

531
00:28:13,420 --> 00:28:17,290
我要做的有很多  这点我们之前已经谈过
Well, I plan to do a lot. And we talked about this earlier.

532
00:28:17,290 --> 00:28:18,130
首先  最重要的是
First and foremost,

533
00:28:18,130 --> 00:28:21,050
我想推动男女平等
I want to press for gender equality

534
00:28:21,050 --> 00:28:22,850
消除薪资差距
and close the salary gap.

535
00:28:22,850 --> 00:28:24,980
如果一半的就业人员
If half of the working population

536
00:28:24,980 --> 00:28:26,930
能拿到更多的工资
has more money in their pockets,

537
00:28:26,930 --> 00:28:30,000
这会刺激消费  促进经济增长
that will catalyze spending, which will grow the economy,

538
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:32,500
最终创造更多就业机会
which will, in turn, create more jobs.

539
00:28:33,310 --> 00:28:34,590
总统先生  你怎么看
Mr. President, what do you think of that?

540
00:28:34,590 --> 00:28:37,680
我同意这种想法  我认为男女平等非常重要
Oh, I agree. I think that gender equality is very important.

541
00:28:37,680 --> 00:28:39,550
在我主张的《美就法》中
And under my AmWorks program,

542
00:28:39,550 --> 00:28:42,790
会有一项条款  《美就法》下所有的就业岗位
there will be a provision that all AmWorks jobs,

543
00:28:42,790 --> 00:28:46,410
都不能出现男女薪资不平等的情况
there can be no discrepancy in pay between men and women.

544
00:28:46,410 --> 00:28:48,230
《美就法》  这只是政府提供的工作
AmWorks jobs, so that's the government.

545
00:28:48,230 --> 00:28:49,330
那其它的私人企业呢
What about the rest of the private sector?

546
00:28:49,330 --> 00:28:51,420
我认为得先有榜样
Well, I think we have to start by leading by example,

547
00:28:51,420 --> 00:28:52,480
再着手立法...
then we introduce legislation...

548
00:28:52,480 --> 00:28:53,460
榜样
Leading by example?

549
00:28:53,460 --> 00:28:55,830
{\an8}如果《美国就业法案》就是你所谓的榜样
If America Works is how you lead by example...

550
00:28:54,210 --> 00:28:57,570
抱歉  请让我说完  邓巴女士
I'm sorry, please let me finish my point, Mr. Dunbar.

551
00:28:55,830 --> 00:28:57,970
{\an8}如果这就是你所谓的榜样
If that is how you lead by example,

552
00:28:57,970 --> 00:29:00,200
那我们是否要认为  每个人都要非法地
then are we to assume that everyone should illegally

553
00:29:00,200 --> 00:29:02,720
占用他们不该占用的资金
raid funds that they have no right to use?

554
00:29:02,720 --> 00:29:04,820
每个人都要去抢银行吗
Everyone should start robbing banks?

555
00:29:04,820 --> 00:29:06,750
去打劫酒水店吗
Holding up liquor stores?

556
00:29:06,750 --> 00:29:08,500
邓巴女士  无意冒犯
Now, Ms. Dunbar, with all due respect,

557
00:29:08,500 --> 00:29:11,300
你可以尽情地批判我的计划
you can criticize my programs as much as you want,

558
00:29:11,300 --> 00:29:12,960
但要指控我违法...
but to accuse me of illegal activity--

559
00:29:12,960 --> 00:29:15,860
有一件事你无法否认  那就是在宪法上
One thing you can't deny is that I am much more of an authority

560
00:29:15,860 --> 00:29:18,960
我懂的比你多得多  总统先生
on the Constitution than you are, Mr. President.

561
00:29:21,360 --> 00:29:24,190
邓巴女士  我们三个人
Ms. Dunbar, all three of us on this stage

562
00:29:24,190 --> 00:29:26,510
都曾进行过宣誓就职
have taken oaths of office.

563
00:29:26,510 --> 00:29:30,220
我认为我们都捍卫了宪法
I would have to say that we have all defended the Constitution.

564
00:29:30,220 --> 00:29:33,480
宪法不是你一个人的
You don't have some special claim on the Constitution.

565
00:29:33,480 --> 00:29:35,930
宪法属于在座的所有人
The Constitution belongs to everyone in this room

566
00:29:35,940 --> 00:29:38,190
它属于美国的每一位公民
and every citizen in the United States.

567
00:29:42,620 --> 00:29:44,400
但我想问夏普女士
But I would ask Ms. Sharp,

568
00:29:44,400 --> 00:29:46,840
你投票同意废除《美国就业法案》
you voted in favor of dismantling America Works.

569
00:29:46,840 --> 00:29:49,190
这么做是因为你认为该法案
Was that because you thought it was in fact,

570
00:29:49,190 --> 00:29:51,700
如邓巴女士所言  是非法的吗
as Ms. Dunbar says, illegal?

571
00:29:51,710 --> 00:29:54,920
我当时投票废除法案  是因为我想确保
I voted for dismantlement because I wanted to make sure

572
00:29:54,920 --> 00:29:56,500
我们做好了飓风的应对工作
we were prepared for the hurricane,

573
00:29:56,500 --> 00:29:57,880
而不是由于我认为
not because I thought your

574
00:29:57,900 --> 00:30:00,050
你对《斯塔福法案》的解读是非法的
reading of the Stafford Act was illegal per se.

575
00:30:00,060 --> 00:30:03,730
真的吗  你认为总统有权做那种事吗
Honestly, you think the president had a right to do what he did?

576
00:30:03,730 --> 00:30:05,740
这是拨款问题  不是法律问题
It's an appropriations issue, not a legal one.

577
00:30:05,750 --> 00:30:07,030
那他的人格呢
What about his character?

578
00:30:07,030 --> 00:30:09,230
他相当于直接走进联邦应急管理署对大家说
He basically walked into FEMA and said,

579
00:30:09,240 --> 00:30:11,050
"举起手来  告诉我保险库在哪里"
"Stick 'em up and show me where the vault is."

580
00:30:11,050 --> 00:30:13,760
我现在又成抢劫犯了  六抢·安德伍德
So now I'm a bank robber. Six Gun Underwood,

581
00:30:13,760 --> 00:30:16,540
南卡罗莱纳就这么叫我
what they call me in South Carolina.

582
00:30:19,600 --> 00:30:22,260
抱歉  但我不觉得这有什么好笑的
I'm sorry, but I do not find this funny.

583
00:30:22,930 --> 00:30:25,240
要我说你就是伪君子
I say you are a hypocrite.

584
00:30:25,240 --> 00:30:29,130
你声称在乎那些一千万失业人口
You claim to care about the ten million people out of work,

585
00:30:29,130 --> 00:30:32,380
但你却盗用了他们的赈灾基金
but you will steal their Disaster Relief Fund...

586
00:30:31,740 --> 00:30:34,120
{\an8}这是拨款问题  邓巴女士
This is an appropriations issue, Miss Dunbar.

587
00:30:32,380 --> 00:30:37,110
-社会保险和医疗福利  -我来说说什么虚伪
- Social Security and health care. - I'd like to talk about hypocrisy.

588
00:30:34,120 --> 00:30:38,840
{\an8}我们在华盛顿特区创造了五万个工作岗位
We put 50,000 people to work in Washington DC.

589
00:30:37,110 --> 00:30:40,210
希瑟·邓巴想要缩小贫富差距
Heather Dunbar wants to balance the scales

590
00:30:40,220 --> 00:30:41,890
修复失衡的系统
to fix a broken system.

591
00:30:41,890 --> 00:30:45,660
与此同时她却送自己的孩子上私立学校
And yet she sends her own kids to private school.

592
00:30:45,670 --> 00:30:49,140
用的并非她工作所得收入  而是继承的遗产
With money she never earned, but which she inherited.

593
00:30:49,150 --> 00:30:52,010
出身显赫  却高谈贫困问题
Now, it is easy to talk about the problems of the poor

594
00:30:52,010 --> 00:30:53,710
是站着说话不腰疼
with a silver spoon in your mouth.

595
00:30:58,910 --> 00:31:01,370
我是否家境富裕  确实如此
Am I well-off? Absolutely.

596
00:31:01,890 --> 00:31:04,850
罗斯福推行新政时也是如此
So was FDR when he developed the New Deal.

597
00:31:04,850 --> 00:31:08,130
什么时候人的同情心由收入决定了
Since when does one's income determine one's amount of empathy?

598
00:31:08,130 --> 00:31:09,810
你会送你的孩子上公立学校吗
Would you send your kids to public school?

599
00:31:09,810 --> 00:31:11,460
别再提及我们的孩子了
Let's keep our children out of this.

600
00:31:11,460 --> 00:31:14,090
你希望你的孩子赢在起跑线上
You want your kids to have a head start,

601
00:31:14,090 --> 00:31:16,720
胜过那些上公立学校的孩子
to have an advantage over the kids in public schools.

602
00:31:16,720 --> 00:31:19,020
许多收入水平各不相同的美国人
Lots of Americans, of all ranges of income,

603
00:31:19,020 --> 00:31:22,210
都选择送他们的孩子上私立或教区学校
choose to send their children to private or parochial schools.

604
00:31:22,210 --> 00:31:24,880
但你希望你的孩子比其他孩子
But isn't it true that you want your children

605
00:31:24,880 --> 00:31:27,180
更胜一筹  不是吗
to have a leg up on everyone else?

606
00:31:27,180 --> 00:31:31,050
这是平衡差距吗  还是虚伪
Is that balancing the scales? Or is that hypocrisy?

607
00:31:31,060 --> 00:31:34,280
或许  你是根本不想亲自养育他们
Or maybe it's that you didn't want to raise them yourself

608
00:31:34,280 --> 00:31:36,000
才送他们去上寄宿学校
so you sent them to boarding school.

609
00:31:40,060 --> 00:31:42,090
看来你真的很想当总统
You must really want to be president.

610
00:31:43,150 --> 00:31:44,400
我永远都不会
I would never in a million years

611
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:46,490
在辩论中提到你的孩子
bring up your children in a debate.

612
00:31:46,490 --> 00:31:49,380
你想怎样养育他们是你的私事
The way you choose to raise them is your business.

613
00:31:49,940 --> 00:31:53,220
我想给我的孩子最好的一切吗  当然
Do I want the best for my kids? Yes, I do.

614
00:31:53,220 --> 00:31:54,710
我想你也一样
I imagine you're the same way.

615
00:31:54,710 --> 00:31:55,850
希望是如此
I hope you are.

616
00:31:58,440 --> 00:32:00,750
你们两位肯定都是很棒的母亲
Well, I'm sure you're both excellent mothers.

617
00:32:00,750 --> 00:32:02,100
但也许我们该回到
But perhaps we should get back to

618
00:32:02,100 --> 00:32:03,250
-眼前的问题上  -夏普议员女士
- some of the issues at hand. - Congresswoman Sharp

619
00:32:03,250 --> 00:32:05,490
之前提到性别歧视问题
raised the issue of sexism earlier.

620
00:32:05,490 --> 00:32:08,750
这是很重要的问题  需要进行讨论
Now, it is an important point, and we need to address it.

621
00:32:08,750 --> 00:32:11,520
性别歧视不可取  议员女士说得没错
Sexism is wrong. The Congresswoman is correct

622
00:32:11,520 --> 00:32:14,380
不论何种形式的性别歧视都应被视为违法
in saying that all aspects of it should be illegal.

623
00:32:14,380 --> 00:32:16,920
然后她指责我批评克莱尔·安德伍德
And then, she accused me of being sexist

624
00:32:16,920 --> 00:32:18,580
是性别歧视
for criticizing Claire Underwood.

625
00:32:18,580 --> 00:32:21,460
但这个逻辑放到你身上不也成立吗  夏普女士
But wouldn't that same logic hold true for you, Ms. Sharp?

626
00:32:21,460 --> 00:32:24,100
如果我是男人你还会紧咬我的孩子不放吗
Would you have come after my kids if I were a man?

627
00:32:24,480 --> 00:32:27,270
你不就是想把我抹黑成一个糟糕的母亲
Aren't you trying to paint the picture that I'm a bad mother,

628
00:32:27,270 --> 00:32:30,010
把自己的孩子送去个偏远的地方
shipping my kids off to some far-flung place?

629
00:32:30,010 --> 00:32:33,040
因为你知道如果你能把我抹黑成一个坏母亲
Because you know if you can make me seem like a bad mother,

630
00:32:33,040 --> 00:32:35,930
不可能还会有人支持我
then how could anyone possibly support me?

631
00:32:36,920 --> 00:32:40,490
这不是正面攻击  这只让人恶心
That's not hardball, that is just disgusting.

632
00:32:46,640 --> 00:32:49,500
我必须说我认为邓巴女士说得有道理
Well, I have to say I do think Ms. Dunbar has a point.

633
00:32:49,500 --> 00:32:51,020
说到虚伪
I mean, speaking of hypocrisy,

634
00:32:51,020 --> 00:32:53,110
你不是也送自己的孩子上私立学校吗
don't you send your own kids to private school,

635
00:32:53,110 --> 00:32:54,230
议员女士
Congresswoman?

636
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:00,490
那不是我的论点  我...
Well, that wasn't my point. I--

637
00:33:00,490 --> 00:33:01,770
你的论点是什么
What was your point?

638
00:33:04,790 --> 00:33:05,940
我
Well, I was, um...

639
00:33:07,830 --> 00:33:09,670
我的论点...
My... My point....

640
00:33:18,630 --> 00:33:21,970
约翰  我想在这个议题上我该说的都说完了
John, I think I've said all I need to say on this subject.

641
00:33:21,970 --> 00:33:23,340
那好吧  议员女士
All right, fair enough, Congresswoman.

642
00:33:23,340 --> 00:33:25,420
下个问题是问你的  邓巴女士
Next question goes to you, Ms. Dunbar.

643
00:33:29,360 --> 00:33:30,980
好了  观众们  第一轮民调结果出来了
Okay, guys, first poll is coming in.

644
00:33:29,390 --> 00:33:32,430
{\pos(76.5,213.3)}{\an1}{\pos(75,211.95)}乔治·斯蒂芬诺伯罗斯
ABC新闻首席主播

645
00:33:30,980 --> 00:33:32,920
大多数都支持弗兰克·安德伍德
Most of them give Frank Underwood the win.

646
00:33:32,810 --> 00:33:37,270
{\pos(310.8,45.45)}{\pos(282.6,31.5)}爱荷华州
民主党辩论

647
00:33:32,920 --> 00:33:34,160
但优势并不明显
Not by a lot.

648
00:33:34,160 --> 00:33:37,010
但他所做的能打败邓巴  在竞选中领跑吗
But did he do enough to overtake Dunbar, become the front-runner?

649
00:33:37,010 --> 00:33:39,440
乔治  我认为关键并不在于安德伍德做了什么
George, I don't think it's so much what Underwood did,

650
00:33:38,890 --> 00:33:41,440
{\pos(76.5,214.65)}{\an1}{\pos(75,211.95)}马修·道得
ABC新闻政治撰稿人

651
00:33:39,440 --> 00:33:40,380
而是他没做什么
but what he didn't do.

652
00:33:40,380 --> 00:33:41,900
他保持了总统的气度
He remained presidential.

653
00:33:41,900 --> 00:33:44,980
当他被攻击时  他保持了风度
And when the attacks came his way, he held the high ground.

654
00:33:44,980 --> 00:33:47,520
邓巴和夏普都出击凌厉
Now, Dunbar and Sharp, they came out swinging,

655
00:33:47,530 --> 00:33:48,520
我认为这对她们都不利
and I think it hurt them both.

656
00:33:48,520 --> 00:33:50,050
没错  但夏普必须有所作为
Yeah, but Sharp had to do something.

657
00:33:50,050 --> 00:33:51,690
她落后其他两人20%
She's 20 points behind the other two.

658
00:33:51,690 --> 00:33:54,380
但性别歧视的论调  还攻击邓巴的孩子
But the sexism thing? And going after Dunbar's kids?

659
00:33:53,410 --> 00:33:55,740
{\pos(75.3,215.1)}{\an1}{\pos(75,211.95)}唐娜·布里奇尔
民主党竞选策略顾问

660
00:33:54,380 --> 00:33:55,520
感觉很孤注一掷
It seemed quite desperate.

661
00:33:55,520 --> 00:33:57,240
她确实对邓巴造成了一些伤害
She did do some damage to Dunbar.

662
00:33:57,240 --> 00:34:00,590
这我不敢肯定  邓巴的情况本可能糟
I don't know about that. Dunbar could've fared far worse.

663
00:34:00,590 --> 00:34:02,830
她承受住了打击  也主动出击
She took it on the chin, held her own,

664
00:34:02,830 --> 00:34:04,630
在我看来这是平局
and in my opinion, it was a tie.

665
00:34:04,630 --> 00:34:07,100
但最重要的是这场辩论会带来什么改变吗
But bottom line, does this debate change anything?

666
00:34:07,100 --> 00:34:08,090
这会影响党团会议结果吗
Does it affect the caucus,

667
00:34:08,090 --> 00:34:09,560
这会影响新罕布什尔的初选吗
Does it affect the primary in New Hampshire?

668
00:34:09,560 --> 00:34:11,100
现在离投票还有一个月
We're still over a month out.

669
00:34:11,100 --> 00:34:13,190
这段时间里还有很多变数
And so a lot could change in this process,

670
00:34:13,190 --> 00:34:16,520
但我认为现在的形势对安德伍德有利
but I do think the momentum could shift in Underwood's favor.

671
00:34:16,520 --> 00:34:19,910
让我们别忘记  值得注意的是  现任总统
Let's not forget that it's remarkable that a sitting president

672
00:34:19,910 --> 00:34:21,870
原本并非竞选中的领跑者
isn't considered the front-runner to begin with.

673
00:34:21,870 --> 00:34:22,970
提得很好
That's an excellent point.

674
00:34:22,980 --> 00:34:26,000
从未有过现任总统  要从这么落后的位置往上拼
No incumbent has ever had to fight back from this far...

675
00:34:32,830 --> 00:34:35,120
-喂  -他说她不接电话  先生
- Yes? - He said she's not picking up, sir.

676
00:34:35,480 --> 00:34:37,190
需要我叫他去敲她门吗
Would you like me to have him knock on her door?

677
00:34:37,190 --> 00:34:38,740
不用了  谢谢
No, that's all right. Thank you.

678
00:34:53,600 --> 00:34:55,020
你什么话都没说
You haven't said a word.

679
00:34:59,550 --> 00:35:00,920
你准备辩论几天了
Well, you've been prepping for days.

680
00:35:00,920 --> 00:35:03,250
我觉得你会想静一静
I thought you might want a break from talking.

681
00:35:05,850 --> 00:35:07,550
你对我很失望
You're disappointed in me.

682
00:35:09,000 --> 00:35:10,820
因为孩子被提到了
That the kids got mentioned.

683
00:35:13,080 --> 00:35:14,700
他们还小  没事的
They're teenagers. They'll be fine.

684
00:35:14,700 --> 00:35:18,780
估计还很激动自己被提到了
Probably thrilled... that they got mentioned at all.

685
00:35:21,530 --> 00:35:22,680
要说我对谁失望
If I'm disappointed in anyone,

686
00:35:22,680 --> 00:35:25,140
也是对他把你往火坑里推失望
it's him, for throwing you under the bus.

687
00:35:32,350 --> 00:35:34,200
我今晚跟你一块飞回去
I gotta fly back with you tonight.

688
00:35:34,910 --> 00:35:36,270
你明天不是还有活动吗
Don't you have events tomorrow?

689
00:35:36,710 --> 00:35:37,950
这事更重要
This is more important.

690
00:35:39,470 --> 00:35:40,330
什么事
What is?

691
00:35:54,410 --> 00:35:58,120
{\pos(114,135.45)}献血中心

692
00:36:06,550 --> 00:36:07,890
感谢大家前来
Thank you all for coming in.

693
00:36:07,890 --> 00:36:09,470
请从这边出口出去
If you want to head out this door right here.

694
00:36:10,800 --> 00:36:11,920
非常感谢
Thank you very much.

695
00:36:13,800 --> 00:36:16,380
好了  我就不打扰你了
All right, I'll give you some privacy.

696
00:36:16,380 --> 00:36:17,700
大概只需15分钟
This should only take 15 minutes.

697
00:36:17,700 --> 00:36:20,410
-有需要就叫我们  -谢谢你
- So just holler out if you need anything. - Thank you.

698
00:36:23,270 --> 00:36:25,750
拿把椅子来  我们可以边等边聊
Pull up a chair. We can talk while this finishes up.

699
00:36:29,260 --> 00:36:30,610
我也应该献个血
I should be doing this, too.

700
00:36:32,570 --> 00:36:35,030
这里应该够再放把躺椅
I'm sure we could get another lawn chair in here.

701
00:36:35,520 --> 00:36:38,410
我不能献血  以前有毒瘾
I can't. I was a junkie once upon a time.

702
00:36:42,170 --> 00:36:45,070
你管这叫什么颜色  猩红色不贴切
What would you call this color? Scarlet isn't right.

703
00:36:45,070 --> 00:36:46,600
也不是深红或褐红
It's not crimson or maroon.

704
00:36:46,600 --> 00:36:49,000
-洋红色  -洋红色吗
- Carmine. - Carmine?

705
00:36:49,460 --> 00:36:50,820
果然作家就是不一样
You must be a writer.

706
00:36:51,800 --> 00:36:54,210
不  我知道  但她总跟别人说
No, I know that. But you know she always tells everyone

707
00:36:54,210 --> 00:36:56,850
她都是自己烤的  但我知道肯定不是
she bakes them herself and I know she doesn't.

708
00:36:58,510 --> 00:36:59,610
这是本地的
That's local.

709
00:36:59,990 --> 00:37:02,720
谢谢你的支持  等我到了之后见
Thank you for your support. I'll see you when I get there.

710
00:37:02,720 --> 00:37:05,120
为什么我们不能在电话里谈
Is there some reason we couldn't do this by phone?

711
00:37:05,420 --> 00:37:06,850
这需要当面谈清楚
This needed to be in person.

712
00:37:06,860 --> 00:37:08,630
是  但你把你的活动都取消了
Yes, but you canceled all your events.

713
00:37:08,630 --> 00:37:10,220
我想跟你谈谈辩论的事
I want to talk about the debate.

714
00:37:10,220 --> 00:37:12,510
虽然不是我们期望中的大获全胜
You know, it wasn't the home run we hoped for,

715
00:37:12,510 --> 00:37:13,760
但你干得不错  杰姬
but you did great, Jackie.

716
00:37:13,760 --> 00:37:15,670
她一半时间都在防守辩护
She spent half the debate on the defensive.

717
00:37:15,670 --> 00:37:17,130
我让自己难堪了
I humiliated myself.

718
00:37:17,130 --> 00:37:18,810
你只是受了点挫败
You got a little beat up, that's all.

719
00:37:18,810 --> 00:37:20,800
而你下了最重的一拳
And you threw the biggest punch.

720
00:37:20,800 --> 00:37:22,410
你是说你孩子的事吗
Oh, you mean the thing about your kids?

721
00:37:22,410 --> 00:37:23,590
那不是我们说好的
That wasn't what we discussed.

722
00:37:23,590 --> 00:37:26,080
我必须对你下重手  这样她就不能了
I had to hit you hard so she wouldn't.

723
00:37:26,080 --> 00:37:28,700
再说  我们得打消
And besides, we had to dispel any suspicion

724
00:37:28,700 --> 00:37:30,160
我俩串通的猜疑
that you and I might be in concert.

725
00:37:30,170 --> 00:37:33,410
我不喜欢我们现在的这种关系
I'm not comfortable with the dynamic we've established.

726
00:37:36,420 --> 00:37:38,300
什么关系
What dynamic is that?

727
00:37:38,310 --> 00:37:40,600
你拴着我得那条绳索
The leash you have me on.

728
00:37:40,600 --> 00:37:44,130
我得对你言听计从
How I'm supposed to roll over and do any trick you want.

729
00:37:44,640 --> 00:37:46,370
你是不把我当回事
You're taking me for granted.

730
00:37:47,630 --> 00:37:49,710
不然呢  我该怎么着
What, am I supposed to be, uh...

731
00:37:49,720 --> 00:37:52,880
感激你那乏善可陈的热情
appreciative of your lackluster enthusiasm?

732
00:37:52,880 --> 00:37:59,480
你"算是"跟我一队是我天大的幸运吗
How fortunate I am to have you "sort of" on my team?

733
00:38:00,760 --> 00:38:03,640
你不喜欢我们之间的关系
You're not "happy" with our dynamic?

734
00:38:03,640 --> 00:38:06,660
我还不喜欢你的态度
Well, I'm not happy with your attitude.

735
00:38:06,660 --> 00:38:09,270
要说起来  也是你不把我当回事
If anything, you're taking me for granted.

736
00:38:09,270 --> 00:38:11,860
-先生  -我们有约定  杰姬
- Sir-- - We had a deal, Jackie.

737
00:38:12,430 --> 00:38:15,220
我很乐意履行约定
And I am perfectly willing to hold up my end of the bargain.

738
00:38:15,230 --> 00:38:17,670
但别想错了
But do not be under any illusions.

739
00:38:17,670 --> 00:38:19,940
这种合作关系并不平等
This is not a partnership of equals.

740
00:38:19,940 --> 00:38:21,480
完全不平等
Nothing close to it.

741
00:38:21,480 --> 00:38:25,700
你要是想当我的副总统  就得按我说的做
If you are to be my Vice President, you will do what I ask.

742
00:38:25,700 --> 00:38:26,680
我们不能每次
And we will not

743
00:38:26,680 --> 00:38:30,500
因为你对我的要求有所不情愿
have this conversation every time you feel uncomfortable

744
00:38:30,500 --> 00:38:31,920
或不满我的行为
with what I ask you to do,

745
00:38:31,920 --> 00:38:34,830
就要这样争执一番
or how I choose to conduct myself.

746
00:38:35,910 --> 00:38:38,010
这就是我们的关系
That's our dynamic.

747
00:38:46,080 --> 00:38:47,410
我们还要按原时间表来吗
Are we still sticking to the timeline?

748
00:38:47,420 --> 00:38:48,980
对不起  我听不太清
I'm sorry, I couldn't quite hear you.

749
00:38:48,980 --> 00:38:51,160
我们还要按原时间表来吗  我下周退出
Are we still sticking to the timeline? I drop out next week?

750
00:38:51,160 --> 00:38:52,850
没理由不这么做
I see no reason why you shouldn't.

751
00:38:52,850 --> 00:38:54,960
-谢谢您  总统先生  -爱荷华见
- Thank you, Mr. President. - See you in Iowa.

752
00:38:57,270 --> 00:38:59,550
你怎么又把头发染回金色了
Why did you change your hair back to blonde?

753
00:38:59,550 --> 00:39:01,190
这就是你最想问的吗
That's your burning question?

754
00:39:02,010 --> 00:39:03,250
只是好奇
I'm curious.

755
00:39:04,740 --> 00:39:06,200
这对书有什么帮助
How does that help the book?

756
00:39:06,620 --> 00:39:09,050
谁知道呢  但现在我什么灵感都没有
Who knows? But right now, I got nothing.

757
00:39:10,480 --> 00:39:13,480
我们换回金发是因为选民更喜欢金发
We changed it because blonde polls better with the voters.

758
00:39:13,480 --> 00:39:14,150
我们
We?

759
00:39:16,730 --> 00:39:18,840
有一群人
There's a whole gaggle of people

760
00:39:18,840 --> 00:39:21,530
来提议你的造型  穿着
that weigh in on how you look, and what you wear,

761
00:39:22,740 --> 00:39:24,580
考虑活动需要什么
whether an event calls for...

762
00:39:25,680 --> 00:39:27,400
高跟鞋  戴不戴耳环
heels, earrings, no earrings.

763
00:39:27,400 --> 00:39:28,670
你讨厌这样  不是吗
You hate it, don't you?

764
00:39:29,970 --> 00:39:31,290
竞选
Campaigning?

765
00:39:31,290 --> 00:39:33,280
没人喜欢竞选过程
Everybody hates campaigning.

766
00:39:33,770 --> 00:39:36,450
除了政客  他们能从中吸取能量
Except for the politicians. They feed off the energy.

767
00:39:36,920 --> 00:39:38,190
还有从他们配偶那儿
And their spouses.

768
00:39:39,690 --> 00:39:41,600
你觉得弗兰西斯在吸食我吗
You think Francis feeds off me?

769
00:39:42,000 --> 00:39:44,410
你可正在献血呢
You are literally giving your blood.

770
00:39:44,410 --> 00:39:47,260
很多配偶不是政客的人也献血
Plenty of people give blood who aren't married to politicians.

771
00:39:48,280 --> 00:39:52,040
没几个人会帮刚炒了自己的人竞选
Very few people campaign for someone who just fired them.

772
00:39:55,110 --> 00:39:56,180
他告诉你的
He tell you that?

773
00:39:56,680 --> 00:39:57,840
他说他背叛了你
He said he betrayed you.

774
00:39:58,510 --> 00:40:00,760
三天后  你染回金发
Three days later, you change your hair back to blonde

775
00:40:00,990 --> 00:40:04,190
然后辞职  以便"投入竞选"
and resign so you can, quote, "devote yourself to the campaign."

776
00:40:05,700 --> 00:40:06,740
一想就明白了
I did the math.

777
00:40:09,590 --> 00:40:11,670
你和弗兰西斯  你们...
You and Francis, you've....

778
00:40:13,450 --> 00:40:14,330
我们怎么
We've what?

779
00:40:18,850 --> 00:40:20,210
他跟你说了很多
He's shared a lot.

780
00:40:22,050 --> 00:40:23,080
会困扰你吗
Does that bother you?

781
00:40:24,510 --> 00:40:25,340
为什么会
Why would it?

782
00:40:26,820 --> 00:40:28,000
这也是背叛吗
Another betrayal?

783
00:40:28,970 --> 00:40:29,720
不是
No.

784
00:40:30,940 --> 00:40:31,800
你...
You're...

785
00:40:38,330 --> 00:40:39,240
你没事吧
Are you okay?

786
00:40:40,430 --> 00:40:41,920
只是有点头晕
Just a little light-headed.

787
00:40:48,280 --> 00:40:49,120
-给  -谢谢
- Here. - Thank you.

788
00:41:01,430 --> 00:41:02,540
我在想
I was thinking.

789
00:41:03,370 --> 00:41:04,340
想什么
About what?

790
00:41:07,880 --> 00:41:09,020
安德伍德夫人
Mrs. Underwood?

791
00:41:09,280 --> 00:41:10,270
跳下去
Jumping.

792
00:41:13,010 --> 00:41:13,880
跳下去
Jumping?

793
00:41:15,210 --> 00:41:16,980
你有过那种感觉吗
You ever have that feeling?

794
00:41:16,980 --> 00:41:19,800
-谈话时  -什么感觉
- Conversation? - Which feeling?

795
00:41:21,260 --> 00:41:25,210
站在桥上  向下看...
On a bridge, you look over and...

796
00:41:26,530 --> 00:41:28,190
往后退
step back.

797
00:41:30,660 --> 00:41:32,330
要帮你叫人吗
Do you need me to get someone?

798
00:41:34,560 --> 00:41:36,660
他求婚时  我说...
He proposed and I said...

799
00:41:38,030 --> 00:41:39,550
我说七年
I said seven years.

800
00:41:43,230 --> 00:41:46,090
七年后如果没问题  就再七年
If it's still good, another seven.

801
00:41:46,100 --> 00:41:47,160
如果不行...
If not...

802
00:41:50,740 --> 00:41:52,390
每七年审视一次
Every seven years.

803
00:41:56,250 --> 00:41:57,680
我不讨厌竞选活动
I don't hate campaigning.

804
00:41:59,570 --> 00:42:01,000
我厌恶的是...
What I hate is...

805
00:42:06,210 --> 00:42:07,630
我有多需要我们
how much I need us.

806
00:42:09,080 --> 00:42:10,570
你们有多需要彼此
How much you need each other?

807
00:42:16,070 --> 00:42:17,180
我没跳下去
I didn't jump.

808
00:42:18,640 --> 00:42:20,160
也没后退
I didn't step back.

809
00:42:24,930 --> 00:42:25,830
我没有...
I didn't...

810
00:42:27,010 --> 00:42:28,020
安德伍德夫人
Mrs. Underwood?

811
00:42:33,290 --> 00:42:34,940
-怎么了  -她晕了
- What happened? - She passed out.

812
00:42:34,940 --> 00:42:36,600
我看看  安德伍德夫人
Let me see. Mrs. Underwood?

813
00:42:36,600 --> 00:42:39,500
能听到吗  安德伍德夫人
Can you hear me? Mrs. Underwood?

814
00:42:39,500 --> 00:42:41,910
这三个姑娘  爸爸不是一个人还是怎么
So all these three girls, they got a different papi or what?

815
00:42:41,910 --> 00:42:46,320
一个金发  一个红发  一个黑发
They got the blonde, they got the redhead, they got the brunette.

816
00:42:46,320 --> 00:42:48,510
-这是《裙路口》的剧情吧  -先生
- And that's Petticoat Junction, right? - Sir?

817
00:42:49,690 --> 00:42:51,960
-能私谈吗  -那我走了
- May we speak privately? - Oh, let me let y'all be.

818
00:42:51,960 --> 00:42:53,350
别啊  弗莱迪  你故事正讲到一半
No, Freddie. You're in the middle of your story.

819
00:42:53,350 --> 00:42:54,880
先生  我想跟你私谈
Sir, if you don't mind.

820
00:42:54,880 --> 00:42:56,620
-是机密吗  -不是
- Is it classified? - No, it is not.

821
00:42:56,620 --> 00:42:57,960
那就说
Then talk.

822
00:42:58,760 --> 00:43:01,160
杰姬刚来我办公室  她很沮丧
Jackie just stopped by my office. She's upset.

823
00:43:02,190 --> 00:43:04,500
我觉得我们该更照顾她的想法
I think we need to take her views more into consideration.

824
00:43:04,500 --> 00:43:06,000
她在无理取闹
She's being ridiculous.

825
00:43:06,000 --> 00:43:07,930
我觉得她挺有道理
I think she made some valid points.

826
00:43:10,600 --> 00:43:14,000
你为我还是为她工作
Who do you work for, me or her?

827
00:43:14,330 --> 00:43:16,140
我只是想转达她的担忧
I'm just trying to communicate her concerns.

828
00:43:16,140 --> 00:43:18,170
她最好照说照做  你也是
She'd better get in line and so had you.

829
00:43:18,170 --> 00:43:20,300
如果总要费时间跟下属解释
I'm never gonna win if I have to spend my time

830
00:43:20,300 --> 00:43:21,990
我是赢不了的
explaining myself to my subordinates.

831
00:43:21,990 --> 00:43:24,540
-我还是走吧  -别  弗莱迪  坐下
- Look, let me let you-- - No, no. Now, Freddy, sit down.

832
00:43:24,540 --> 00:43:27,150
记得我们谈过你是怎样对待下属的吗
Do you remember when we talked about how you treat your staff?

833
00:43:27,850 --> 00:43:29,050
你想获胜吗
You want to win?

834
00:43:29,560 --> 00:43:31,620
没有他们  你绝对做不到
You sure as hell won't do it without any of them.

835
00:43:31,620 --> 00:43:33,450
你继续这样  他们都会离开
You keep on like this, you won't have any of them left.

836
00:43:33,450 --> 00:43:34,840
你想谈忠诚吗
Are you talking about loyalty?

837
00:43:34,840 --> 00:43:37,520
我只接受无条件的忠诚
The only brand of that I accept is unconditional.

838
00:43:37,520 --> 00:43:40,160
-做不到就...  -这应该做收费节目
- Anything less is a-- - Y'all should put this on pay-per-view.

839
00:43:41,380 --> 00:43:44,740
你个头挺大  但这家伙
But you. You a big guy. But this sucker,

840
00:43:44,740 --> 00:43:48,510
我见过他吃肋排狼吞虎咽的样子
I've seen him go through a rack of ribs like it was wet tissue.

841
00:43:48,510 --> 00:43:49,530
你赌谁赢
Who'd you put your money on?

842
00:43:49,530 --> 00:43:51,120
我才不会上当
Oh, I'm not gonna fall into that trap.

843
00:43:51,120 --> 00:43:53,990
-当然是你  -先生  您妻子出事了
- You. - Sir? It's your wife.

844
00:43:53,990 --> 00:43:55,720
-她献血晕过去了  -什么
- She passed out giving blood. - What?

845
00:43:55,720 --> 00:43:58,010
没什么大碍  但耶茨先生打过来了
She's okay, but, uh, Mr. Yates is on the line.

846
00:43:58,010 --> 00:43:59,770
我在私人书房接
I'll take it in my private study.

847
00:44:04,380 --> 00:44:07,330
你这么顶撞他毫无益处
Don't do no good callin' a man out like that.

848
00:44:07,330 --> 00:44:11,360
这就像怪蛇有毒牙
It's like... blamin' a snake for having fangs.

849
00:44:11,360 --> 00:44:12,660
我忍不住
I couldn't help myself.

850
00:44:14,100 --> 00:44:16,310
-能帮我个忙吗  -什么
- Could you do me a favor? - What's that?

851
00:44:16,310 --> 00:44:20,040
帮我打掩护  他让我陪但我还有工作
Cover for me. I got work to do and he needs company.

852
00:44:20,040 --> 00:44:22,400
原来在餐馆  我听腻了
Back at the ribs joint, I could just walk back in the kitchen

853
00:44:22,400 --> 00:44:24,390
就回厨房干活儿
when I got tired of hearing him talk.

854
00:44:24,390 --> 00:44:27,420
-好  我就说你上司来了  -谢谢  伙计
- Yeah. I'll tell him your boss came over. - Thank you, brother.

855
00:44:44,320 --> 00:44:45,620
让她接我电话
Put her on the phone with me.

856
00:44:45,620 --> 00:44:47,740
她不让我打电话  但我觉得应该打
She didn't want me to call, but I thought I should.

857
00:44:47,750 --> 00:44:50,780
-她在旁边吗  -她好像是不好意思
- Well, is she nearby? - I think she's embarrassed.

858
00:44:50,780 --> 00:44:52,500
我可是她丈夫
I'm her husband.

859
00:44:52,500 --> 00:44:53,720
护士在照顾她
The nurses are with her.

860
00:44:54,390 --> 00:44:55,990
也许你还是再等等吧
Maybe you should just hold off for a few minutes.

861
00:44:55,990 --> 00:44:58,700
让她的安保队长立刻送她上飞机
Tell the head of her detail to get her on the plane right away.

862
00:44:58,700 --> 00:45:01,870
她得回来看白宫的医生
She has to come back here and see the White House physician.

863
00:45:01,870 --> 00:45:03,520
我猜如果取消活动的话
My guess is she'd be even more embarrassed

864
00:45:03,520 --> 00:45:04,890
她会更不好意思
if she had to cancel her events.

865
00:45:04,900 --> 00:45:06,440
这跟她的感受无关
This isn't about how she feels.

866
00:45:06,440 --> 00:45:07,960
这是为她好
This is about what's best for her.

867
00:45:07,960 --> 00:45:11,150
她不需要看医生  她需要你
She doesn't need a doctor. She needs you.

868
00:45:11,660 --> 00:45:12,570
这是什么意思
What do you mean?

869
00:45:13,570 --> 00:45:16,390
她说了些话  说到七年一次
She said some things, about every seven years.

870
00:45:16,390 --> 00:45:20,520
还有站在桥边
About being in limbo, on the edge of a bridge.

871
00:45:20,520 --> 00:45:22,450
听着  就因为我告诉过你
Listen, just because I may have shared with you

872
00:45:22,460 --> 00:45:24,040
一些我们婚姻的事
a few things about our marriage

873
00:45:24,040 --> 00:45:26,300
并不代表你可以指手画脚
does not give you the right to interfere with it.

874
00:45:26,300 --> 00:45:28,240
让她好点了给我打电话
Now, please have her call me when she's ready.

875
00:45:34,300 --> 00:45:37,550
结束了
Well... this is it.

876
00:45:37,550 --> 00:45:40,520
-60天  -60天
- Sixty days. - Sixty days.

877
00:45:41,760 --> 00:45:43,240
那电影吓死我了
That movie freaked me out.

878
00:45:44,940 --> 00:45:47,220
全世界可以在60天内分崩离析
The whole world can fall apart in sixty days.

879
00:45:48,750 --> 00:45:50,210
也可以让人彻底戒酒
Or a guy can get sober.

880
00:45:50,680 --> 00:45:53,310
昨晚睡前我洗了十分钟的手
I washed my hands for ten minutes last night before bed.

881
00:45:53,970 --> 00:45:56,220
你把我从酒鬼改造成了洁癖
You turned me from an alcoholic to a germaphobe.

882
00:45:57,200 --> 00:45:58,480
这交易你不吃亏
That's not a bad trade-off.

883
00:45:59,600 --> 00:46:01,650
过去我自己度过的14年
The 14 years I got by on my own...

884
00:46:03,120 --> 00:46:04,760
跟与你一起度过的这八周比
they mean nothing compared to the last eight weeks

885
00:46:04,760 --> 00:46:06,010
根本一文不值
you've been here with me.

886
00:46:08,430 --> 00:46:09,890
换做是我你也会这么做
You would have done the same for me.

887
00:46:11,300 --> 00:46:12,590
我希望我能做到
I'd like to think so.

888
00:46:14,320 --> 00:46:15,160
你会的
Know so.

889
00:46:18,780 --> 00:46:19,860
我爱你  哥哥
I love you, brother.

890
00:46:41,290 --> 00:46:42,760
到了给我打电话
Call me when you land.

891
00:46:43,330 --> 00:46:45,240
老天  你简直跟萨拉一样
Jesus, you sound like Sarah.

892
00:46:58,970 --> 00:47:01,310
我们要在阔德城
So we want to focus on ad-buys

893
00:47:01,310 --> 00:47:04,580
投放更多广告  在得梅因减少投放量
more in the Quad Cities market, less so in Des Moines.

894
00:47:04,580 --> 00:47:05,830
你在东部的支持率更高
You're stronger in the East

895
00:47:05,840 --> 00:47:08,760
我们得巩固那里的领先地位
and we want to turn our twos there into ones.

896
00:47:08,760 --> 00:47:10,690
辩论之后  "愿景"这个口号
The "vision" message really resonated

897
00:47:10,690 --> 00:47:12,250
在焦点小组中引起很大共鸣
in our focus groups post-debate,

898
00:47:12,250 --> 00:47:15,690
我认为我们应该针对此拍个新广告
so I think we should cut a new ad centered on that

899
00:47:15,690 --> 00:47:17,280
并把它纳入竞选宣传
and weave it into the stump.

900
00:47:20,160 --> 00:47:20,940
先生
Sir?

901
00:47:22,660 --> 00:47:23,790
抱歉  什么
I'm sorry, what?

902
00:47:23,790 --> 00:47:25,170
如果我们把竞选宣传的主题
Are you good if we change the stump

903
00:47:25,170 --> 00:47:26,430
换成"愿景"  您没意见吧
to focus on the "vision" theme?

904
00:47:26,430 --> 00:47:28,820
我想明天一早去新罕布什尔
I want to go to New Hampshire tomorrow, first thing.

905
00:47:29,200 --> 00:47:30,150
您的行程安排是去爱荷华州
We have you going to Iowa.

906
00:47:30,150 --> 00:47:31,860
我知道  但我想更改计划
I know, but I want to change the schedule.

907
00:47:32,550 --> 00:47:35,860
任何人竞选时  都得停下脚步评估形势
In every campaign, there comes a time for taking stock.

908
00:47:33,980 --> 00:47:43,980
{\an1}{\pos(143.4,224.1)}夏普竞选团队发表声明

909
00:47:36,230 --> 00:47:38,600
自我反省
A time for soul-searching. And...

910
00:47:38,610 --> 00:47:42,160
在过去的24小时里  我就是那么做的
in the past 24 hours, I have done just that.

911
00:47:42,780 --> 00:47:46,070
而我的决定如下
And the conclusion that I have come to is this:

912
00:47:46,520 --> 00:47:50,580
如果目标是建立一个更安全  兴盛的美国
If the goal is a safer, more prosperous America,

913
00:47:50,920 --> 00:47:53,280
并不非得我参选才能实现
I don't need to run for us to achieve that.

914
00:47:53,610 --> 00:47:58,680
我需要做的  我也鼓励我的支持者做的
All I need to do and what I encourage all of my supporters to do

915
00:47:58,680 --> 00:48:02,810
就是支持希瑟·邓巴成为美国总统
is to help elect Heather Dunbar to the White House.

916
00:48:03,920 --> 00:48:07,080
-叛徒婊子  -虽然我的竞选结束了
- Judas bitch. - While I may be ending my camp--

917
00:48:12,950 --> 00:48:15,790
我就是生气  如果冒犯你了我很抱歉
I'm just pissed off. I'm sorry if I offended.

918
00:48:17,930 --> 00:48:19,630
不知道她给了她什么好处
Yeah, I wonder what she offered her.

919
00:48:20,330 --> 00:48:21,150
什么都没有
Nothing.

920
00:48:21,900 --> 00:48:22,880
得了
Yeah, right.

921
00:48:24,070 --> 00:48:25,690
我确定
I know for a fact.

922
00:48:27,180 --> 00:48:28,500
这事你早就知道吗
You knew about this?

923
00:48:37,660 --> 00:48:39,100
你应该给总统打电话
You should call the President.

924
00:48:56,470 --> 00:49:00,880
"一只浑身是毛  超级可怕的狼蛛  名叫蒂娜
"A very hairy, terribly scary tarantula named Tina.

925
00:49:00,880 --> 00:49:03,780
我是在纽约一个鞋盒里发现她的
I found her in a shoebox in New York City.

926
00:49:03,780 --> 00:49:06,460
我刚发现蒂娜时吓得直叫"
When I first saw Tina I shrieked..."

927
00:49:07,820 --> 00:49:09,080
你害怕吗
Were you scared?

928
00:49:09,080 --> 00:49:11,320
我吓死了
Oh, I was terribly scared.

929
00:49:12,330 --> 00:49:14,760
"蒂娜从左脚的鞋里伸出头来"
"Tina had poked her head up out of the left shoe..."

930
00:49:14,760 --> 00:49:17,850
-我不知道你要来  -她也不知道
- I didn't know you were coming. - She doesn't either.

931
00:49:18,470 --> 00:49:21,690
"所以我呆在那儿  不知道该怎么办
"So there I was, not knowing what to believe.

932
00:49:21,690 --> 00:49:25,530
我该让蒂娜待在鞋盒里还是放她出来"
Should I leave Tina in the shoebox or set Tina free?"

933
00:49:25,530 --> 00:49:27,700
-把她留在鞋盒里  -放她出来
- Leave her in the box! - Set her free!

934
00:49:27,700 --> 00:49:29,480
-放她出来  -把她留在鞋盒里
- Set her free! - Leave her in the box!

935
00:49:29,480 --> 00:49:31,150
我的天  我不知道该怎么办
Oh, my Goodness! I don't know what to do!

936
00:49:31,150 --> 00:49:32,700
什么都不做  不要管她
Nothing! Do nothing!

937
00:49:32,700 --> 00:49:35,120
-我该怎么办  -先生  格雷森先生找您
- What should I do? - Sir, Mr. Grayson needs to speak with you.

938
00:49:35,120 --> 00:49:37,270
-告诉他我会打回去  -他说这事很重要
- Tell him I'll call him back. - He says it's important.

939
00:49:37,270 --> 00:49:39,210
之后再说  我在陪我夫人
Later. I'm with my wife.

940
00:49:40,860 --> 00:49:42,870
我不知道该怎么办
I don't know what to do!

941
00:49:43,440 --> 00:49:45,420
你什么都不该做
You shouldn't do anything.

942
00:49:45,920 --> 00:49:48,030
-放她出来  -什么都不做吗
- Let her out! - Don't do anything?

943
00:49:54,490 --> 00:50:04,490
{\an5}{\pos(193,145)}美国总统选举  从两党候选人宣布参选  到党内初选
再到最后普选投票  整个过程往往要持续一年半多
在这漫长的一年半中  最戏剧化的环节  就是候选人电视辩论
在党内初选阶段  参加辩论的人数比较多  电视辩论的次数也比较多
电视辩论一般由两党的全国委员会组织筹划  由各大电视台主持
在2012年的大选中  共和党初选阶段共举行了多达20场的电视辩论
由于在初选辩论中党内候选人彼此攻击过于激烈  导致初选结束后
最后胜出的候选人在普选阶段面对对立党派的对手时
已经伤痕累累  落了下风
所以在即将到来的2016总统大选中
共和党全国委员会决定减少电视辩论次数

944
00:50:19,490 --> 00:50:29,490
{\an5}{\pos(193,145)}初选结束后  两党各自提名一名候选人在普选中出战对垒
普选阶段的电视辩论一般只有四场
三场为总统候选人辩论  一场为副总统候选人辩论
辩论的组织工作由专门的总统选举电视辩论委员会负责
在2012年大选中  三场总统辩论中的第一场最为精彩
一向自诩口才出众的奥巴马  由于过于轻敌
在辩论前没有认真准备  而是跑去参观胡佛水坝
结果在辩论开始后被对手罗姆尼占尽上风
在整场辩论中始终处于绝对劣势
辩论结束后  一直在民调中落后的罗姆尼开始反超奥巴马
可惜后来因飓风等因素  罗姆尼将在辩论中获得的优势又拱手让出

